gomodel:SYNGO_1844  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: TrkC and PTPσ Ectodomains Induce Excitatory Presynaptic and Postsynaptic Differentiation, Respectively. Experimental description: 7/11/2017 Pim\n- Species of cultured neurons is not explicitly stated in the paper.\n\nAwait species information (amcraig@interchange.ubc.ca , dd 7/11/2017)\n\n8/11/2017 Pim\n- Authors responded:\nTrkC-Fc protein were purchased from R&D systems ( https://www.rndsystems.com/products/recombinant-human-trkc-fc-chimera-protein-cf_373-tc-cf ). Thus, it's a human TrkC.\n(We also used recombinant proteins of TrkCN366AT369A-Fc in Supplemental Figure S2. This mutated TrkC-Fc is based on rat TrkC (BC078844).)\nneuronal cultures, we used rat primary hippocampal neuron cultures.\n\n- The authors use a combination of rat cells, and human and rat TrkC. I annotate against the rat protein and cells." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1844" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

